FIG. 3 is a cross sectional view of a portion of a SiC bipolar junction transistor with an overgrown p+ base region wherein the base contact layer is used as a mask for etching emitter contact openings in the underlying p+ overgrown base layer according to a second embodiment of the invention;
FIG. 4 is a cross-sectional view of a multi-fingered SiC bipolar junction transistor having overgrown p+ base regions and an overgrown base contact layer wherein emitter contact openings and guard rings have been formed by etching the overgrown base layer using the base contact layer as a mask;
